Page 1: File System & File Basics
Filesystem & Storage
File System:
A file system is the structure used by the OS to store and organize data on a disk
.
Without a file system: Disk = random bits (0s & 1s)
.
With a file system: Disk = organized files + folders
.
Core Concept: File system = organization + management
.
File:
A file is a collection of data stored on a disk
.
Examples of file extensions: .txt, .jpg (image), .png (image), .mp4 (video), .exe (executable)
.
Components of a File: Data + Metadata
.
Metadata includes:
File name
Size
Permission
Owner
Creation time
Location on disk
.

