Page 2: Directory Structure & Storage Allocation
Directory (Folder Structure):
A directory organizes files in a tree structure
.
Hierarchy Example: Root → Home (contains file.txt, file2.txt) and Images (contains photo.png)
.
Internal Storage:
Files are stored internally as blocks in the disk
.
A file is stored in one or more blocks
.
Allocation Algorithms:
Continuous allocation
Indexed file storage
Linked allocation
.
The OS finds a file (e.g., when you execute open("file.txt")) by identifying which blocks contain each part of the file
.

